Vice President Biden will be visiting Serious Materials Chicago on April 27th to discuss how the Recovery Act is creating jobs and building a 21st century economy. Serious Materials acquired the assets of Republic Windows and Doors in February 2009 and announced its intention to reopen the factory and rehire 250 union employees thanks to spending under the Recovery Act. Senators Dick Durbin and Roland Burris, along with Mayor Richard Daley, will also be in attendance. Afterward, the Vice President will speak at the 2009 Richard J. Daley Urban Forum. The event is open to the press, and media details and logistics can be obtained by contacting Ellie Abrams at 312-573-5516.